      "description": "The spec does not define the refund policy: full refund, partial refund, or refund minus fee. It also does not specify refund timing (instant, 3-5 business days, etc.).",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Customers", "Finance/Accounting"],
      "options": [
        "Full refund regardless of state",
        "Full refund pre-assignment, partial refund (minus fee) post-assignment",
        "No refund after assignment"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Option B aligns with fair compensation for both customer and courier. PM and Finance must agree on fee amounts."
    },
    {
      "type": "missing_context",
      "description": "No information about the existing order state machine. The acceptance criteria assume standard logistics states but the actual system may use different states or transitions.",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Engineering", "Product"],
      "options": [
        "Provide the current order state machine diagram or enum definition",
        "Accept the assumed states and adjust during implementation"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Provide the actual state machine. Building cancellation logic against assumed states risks costly rework."
    },
    {
      "type": "missing_context",
      "description": "Promotional order and coupon restoration policy is undefined. When a user cancels an order that used a single-use coupon, is the coupon restored?",
      "affected_stakeholders": ["Customers", "Product/Growth", "Finance"],
      "options": [
        "Always restore coupons on cancellation",
        "Never restore coupons (cancellation forfeits the promotion)",
        "Restore only if cancelled within a grace period"
      ],
      "recommendation": "Restore coupons for cancellations in the fee-free window (pre-assignment). Do not restore for post-assignment cancellations to discourage abuse. PM must confirm."
    }
  ],

